# write_mass_maps.context — High-level logic for src/write_mass_maps.c

Purpose: Help an LLM (or a new contributor) quickly understand how the mass-maps module works end-to-end: inputs, algorithm, data flow, parallelism (OpenMP + MPI), I/O, compile-time knobs, and performance considerations. It summarizes the code; it is not code.

## What this file does (MASS_MAPS)
- Goal: For each adjacent pair of fragmentation outputs (a “segment”), detect when a mass element’s trajectory crosses the past light-cone (PLC), then accumulate one HEALPix map per segment.
- Pipeline per segment:
  1) Build candidate periodic replications whose Lagrangian AABB overlaps the segment’s comoving radial shell [chi_prev, chi_curr].
  2) Optional Lagrangian sub-volume culling: split the local tile into blocks; use padded AABB radial test plus an exact angular test (axis piercing + corner enumeration) to quickly reject block/rep pairs that cannot contribute.
  3) For remaining block/rep pairs, traverse particles, detect PLC entry H = chi(z) − r sign change between endpoints, linearly interpolate entry position, apply aperture filter, pixelize, and accumulate into the segment’s map.
  4) Reduce across MPI tasks and write exactly one FITS per segment (rank 0 performs I/O).

## Key dependencies and prerequisites
- Requires PLC (past light-cone), RECOMPUTE_DISPLACEMENTS, HAVE_CFITSIO at compile time. SNAPSHOT is used by optional filters.
- Displacements are maintained at previous and current endpoints per segment (products array + LPT fields). Under scale-dependent modes, derivatives are recomputed each segment (fragment.c); under scale-independent ΛCDM, a fast rescaling path applies.
- HEALPix via chealpix is used for RING pixelization.

## Runtime parameters (from params)
- params.PLCAperture [deg]: PLC cone aperture; < 180 produces a spherical cap map (Ncap prefix of RING ordering). 180 produces full-sky.
- params.MassMapNSIDE: HEALPix NSIDE for maps.
- params.InterPartDist [Mpc]: particle spacing; defines position units (true Mpc) and informs culling pad reporting.
- params.RunFlag: included in output filenames.
- Cosmology (sigma8, Hubble100) for variable AABB padding and geometry.

## Compile-time toggles (macros)
- MASS_MAPS: enable module (this file).
- PLC: enable PLC logic.
- RECOMPUTE_DISPLACEMENTS: keep prev/curr fields per segment, used by interpolation helper.
- HAVE_CFITSIO: enable FITS I/O.
- SNAPSHOT: products fields used by optional filtering/diagnostics.
- MASS_MAPS_FILTER_UNCOLLAPSED: include only entries with z_plc > z_acc (requires SNAPSHOT and current zacc in products; handled via distribute_back each segment).
- MASS_MAPS_MATCH_DIAG: extra prints to reconcile entries with PLC halo catalog.
- MASS_MAPS_FULLSKY_OUTPUT: also write full-sky IMAGE HDU when aperture < 180 (otherwise only cap BINTABLE is written for caps).
- MASS_MAPS_BLOCKS, MASS_MAPS_BLOCKS_X/Y/Z: number of Lagrangian blocks per axis for culling (default 8 each). 0 disables culling.
- MASS_MAPS_VARPAD_FACTOR: variable AABB pad factor; effective pad_phys ≈ FACTOR · (sigma8/0.8)^{1.5} / (1+z) / H0.
- MASS_MAPS_VARPAD_WARN_FRAC: on last segment, warn if |x(q,z) − q| exceeds pad for more than this fraction.
- MASS_MAPS_THREAD_ACCUM: use per-thread local maps and merge once per block to reduce atomics; otherwise, accumulate with OpenMP atomics into a shared map.
- DISP_HISTOGRAM (+ DISP_HIST_*): optional displacement magnitude histogram per endpoint, MPI-reduced and written as ASCII on rank 0.
- MASS_MAPS_CAP_DIAG: optional cap-boundary diagnostics (max accepted/missed angle, prefix misses). Compiled only when enabled; default off.

## Data model and memory
- Segments (MassSheets): NMassSheets = outputs.n − 1. Each has bounds in redshift and precomputed comoving distances (chi_prev/curr), angular-diameter distances (da), deltas and inverses, and chi^3 span for potential volumetric weights.
- Maps: One HEALPix map per segment, stored in a flat array MassMapSegmentMaps of length NMassSheets × NPIX. For cap mode, NPIX = Ncap; for full-sky, NPIX = 12·NSIDE^2.
- Pixelization basis: PLC axis is cached; a local orthonormal triad (e1,e2,e3) centered at PLC center is used to compute spherical angles and ring indices.
- Temporary: root-only MassMapReduceBuffer for MPI reductions, per-thread LocalMap when MASS_MAPS_THREAD_ACCUM, per-block caches of prev/curr positions when culling is enabled.

## Orchestrator (mass_maps_process_segment)
Inputs and preconditions:
- segment_index in 1..NMassSheets (map index s_map = segment_index − 1). The first segment (index 0) has no crossings and is skipped.
- On entry, ensure products contains current zacc and group_ID if filtering/diagnostics require them; this is done by distribute_back each segment when MASS_MAPS_FILTER_UNCOLLAPSED or matching diagnostics are enabled.

Steps:
1) Lazy allocate HEALPix maps (mass_maps_init_healpix_maps) using params.MassMapNSIDE, compute Ncap for cap mode, and zero maps if first use.
2) Candidate replications (mass_maps_select_segment_replications):
   - For each periodic replication id r, compute replication chi bounds [rmin, rmax] once (mass_maps_replication_chi_bounds) and select those overlapping [chi_prev, chi_curr]. This is a coarse radial prefilter.
3) Precompute replication shifts RepShift[r] = (ii,jj,kk)·Box in phys Mpc for all selected r once.
4) Optional Lagrangian culling path (enabled when MASS_MAPS_BLOCKS_* > 0):
   - Split the local FFT tile (global lattice coords for this rank) into nbx×nby×nbz blocks.
   - Compute unified AABB pad aabb_pad_phys for this segment using MASS_MAPS_VARPAD_FACTOR, sigma8, redshift, and H0. Report pad in Mpc, Mpc/h, and cells.
   - For each block, construct its padded Lagrangian AABB in phys units and cull replications using two tests:
     • Radial shell test: via aabb_distance_bounds_to_point() against the segment shell [chi_prev, chi_curr]. If [dmin,dmax] ∩ [chi_prev,chi_curr] = ∅, reject the block for all reps.
     • Exact angular test: project AABB onto the PLC transverse basis (ex, ey) and check axis piercing (x span contains 0 and y span contains 0). If pierced, early accept (block cannot be wholly outside). Otherwise, enumerate the 8 corners relative to the PLC center, compute cos(theta) at each, and reject only if the maximum corner cosine ≤ cos(aperture).
   - If a block survives for at least one replication, build per-block caches of endpoint positions in phys Mpc: for each particle, load pos_data from products (mass_maps_set_point_from_products_global), then compute absolute prev/curr Eulerian positions with mass_maps_compute_prev_curr_positions (q + LPT displacements assembled to compiled order). Optionally count |Pcurr − Pprev| > aabb_pad_phys diagnostics on last segment.
   - For each passing replication r of this block: loop particles using cached positions, add RepShift[r], test PLC entry via mass_maps_crossing_from_shifted_positions (inside→outside crossing; linear interpolation alpha = H_prev / (H_prev − H_curr) with epsilon guard), check entry against redshift bounds and aperture (mass_maps_entry_inside_aperture), optional uncollapsed-only filter (z_plc > zacc), compute pixel (mass_maps_compute_pixel_from_pos), and accumulate weight (default 1.0) into the segment map.
   - Accumulation strategy:
     • Default: OpenMP atomic updates directly to the shared segment map.
     • MASS_MAPS_THREAD_ACCUM: per-thread LocalMap used within the block; merge into the shared map once per block (reduces atomic contention).
5) Non-culling path: iterate over selected replications first, then all local particles; build pos_data on the fly and compute prev/curr, crossing, aperture, filter, pixelize, and accumulate as above (no per-block caches).
6) MPI reductions and output:
  - Reduce per-rep entry counters, diagnostics, and the segment map to rank 0. Root writes pinocchio.<RunFlag>.massmap.seg%03d.fits via mass_maps_write_segment_map and prints map stats at VDBG level. The FITS includes PLC axis, APERTURE, NSIDE, ORDERING=RING, FIRSTPIX/LASTPIX. For cap maps: a BINTABLE with columns (PIXEL, TEMPERATURE) and INDXSCHM=EXPLICIT; full-sky maps include both primary IMAGE and a HEALPIX BINTABLE extension for compatibility.
   - If MASS_MAPS_FILTER_UNCOLLAPSED is active, write FILTER metadata into FITS (mass_maps_write_filter_keywords): FILTER='ZPLC>ZACC', ZF_CONS/ZF_EXCL/ZF_INCL/ZF_FEXCL, ZPLC_MIN/MAX, ZACC_MIN/MAX, ZPLC_OOS.
7) At the end of the last segment, free temporary buffers; maps remain allocated until explicit free.

Edge conditions and guards:
- First segment (index 0): no crossings (no prev); function returns early.
- Small denominator for alpha (H_prev − H_curr): guarded by epsilon; treat as no crossing.
- If computed Ncap=0 for given NSIDE and aperture, maps are disabled with a warning.
- Out-of-cap pixel indices are guarded; debug prints if any OOB occur.
- Angular culling: early-accept blocks whose transverse projection spans the PLC axis (axis piercing). Otherwise, apply corner enumeration test as above.
- Optional z_plc bounds check: ensure interpolated z_plc lies within [z_prev,z_curr] with tolerance; otherwise count as out-of-segment.

## Core helpers (by role)
Geometry and pixelization:
- aabb_distance_bounds_to_point(minv,maxv,c) → (dmin,dmax): tight Euclidean distance bounds from PLC center to an AABB; used for radial shell culling.
- mass_maps_entry_inside_aperture(pos): quick check against PLC cone aperture.
- mass_maps_compute_pixel_from_pos(pos,nside,ipix*): compute RING pixel index for absolute position using cached PLC basis; used for both full and cap maps (cap uses index prefix).

PLC crossing:
- mass_maps_crossing_from_shifted_positions(Pprev,Pcurr,chi_prev,chi_curr,entry_pos*): detect inside→outside radial crossing H=chi−r with linear interpolation; return entry position if crossing.

Products access and positions:
- mass_maps_set_point_from_products_global(ig,jg,kg,F, pos_data*): fill pos_data with q (global lattice), and LPT displacement components for prev/curr endpoints per compiled order; F=(1+z_curr) helps set weights/scales consistently.
- mass_maps_compute_prev_curr_positions(pos_data*, Pprev[3], Pcurr[3], lpt_order): assemble absolute positions at prev/curr as q + Σ LPT_terms (prev and curr separately); positions are in phys Mpc.
- mass_maps_get_zacc_global(ig,jg,kg): read products[idx].zacc for filters; mass_maps_get_group_id_global similarly returns group_ID.

Segments and maps:
- mass_maps_init_sheets(): build segment array (MassSheets) from outputs; precompute chi/da spans and helpers.
- mass_maps_init_healpix_maps(nside): allocate MassMapSegmentMaps (flat buffer), compute NPIX (full) or Ncap (cap), zero maps; log pixel along axis.
- mass_maps_zero_maps(), mass_maps_free_maps(): reset and cleanup.
- mass_maps_write_segment_map(s): root-only; write FITS per segment with HEALPix metadata. Full-sky: primary IMAGE HDU plus secondary BINTABLE (EXTNAME='HEALPIX') with columns PIXEL,TEMPERATURE. Cap: single BINTABLE with PIXEL,TEMPERATURE (explicit indexing). Adds PLC axis vector, APERTURE, NSIDE, ORDERING, FIRSTPIX,LASTPIX; optional FILTER keywords via mass_maps_write_filter_keywords().
- mass_maps_write_sheet_table(): write pinocchio.<RunFlag>.sheets.out (id,z_lo,z_hi,chi_lo,chi_hi,da_lo,da_hi, etc.) for reproducibility.

Replication selection and culling:
- mass_maps_replication_chi_bounds(rep_id, rmin*, rmax*): compute comoving distance bounds for a periodic replication box w.r.t. PLC center (phys units). Used to build the candidate list per segment.
- mass_maps_select_segment_replications(segment_index): coarse radial prefilter for replications: keep rep if its [rmin,rmax] overlaps [chi_prev,chi_curr]. Angular/aperture culling is deferred to block-level tests for tighter bounds.

Optional diagnostics (compile-time):
- DISP_HISTOGRAM path: per-endpoint displacement magnitude histograms across the local tile with OpenMP reduction; MPI-reduced and written by root to pinocchio.<z>.<RunFlag>.disp_hist.out with VARPAD context in the header (pad in Mpc, Mpc/h, and cells).

## Parallelism model
MPI (distributed memory):
- Domain decomposition is inherited from the FFT/products grid; each rank operates on its local FFT tile only. Most of the work is embarrassingly parallel across ranks. For each segment:
  - Each rank computes its local contributions (candidates, traversals, map updates).
  - Per-rep counters, diagnostics, and the segment map buffer are reduced across ranks to root (rank 0).
  - Only rank 0 writes the FITS outputs and the sheets table; others perform no I/O.

OpenMP (shared memory):
- Used in multiple places:
  - Displacement histogram (if enabled): collapse(3) over local tile, reduction over counters.
  - Culling-enabled path: parallel for collapse(3) over block-grid with dynamic schedule to balance visited blocks. Within each block, optional per-thread LocalMap reduces atomics.
  - Non-culling path: parallelized loops over lattice indices and replications with atomic updates for shared counters and map cells (or local-map merges within critical sections when configured).
- Thread-safety:
  - Map updates: either OpenMP atomics on the shared segment map, or per-thread buffers merged once per block (MASS_MAPS_THREAD_ACCUM) to reduce contention.
  - Small scalar counters use OpenMP atomics; infrequent merges use critical sections.

## I/O outputs and formats
 - Per-segment FITS: pinocchio.<RunFlag>.massmap.seg%03d.fits (rank 0 only).
  - Full-sky mode (aperture=180): dual format for compatibility:
    • Primary IMAGE HDU: array length NPIX=12·NSIDE^2 (RING ordering implied).
    • Secondary BINTABLE (EXTNAME='HEALPIX'): columns PIXEL (0..NPIX-1, int32) and TEMPERATURE (double). INDXSCHM=EXPLICIT. Contains same metadata as IMAGE.
  - Cap mode (aperture<180): single BINTABLE (EXTNAME='HEALPIX') with columns PIXEL (0..Ncap−1) and TEMPERATURE (double). INDXSCHM=EXPLICIT. Metadata: PIXTYPE=HEALPIX, ORDERING=RING, NSIDE, FIRSTPIX, LASTPIX, APERTURE, AXISV1/2/3.
  - Optional FILTER keywords when MASS_MAPS_FILTER_UNCOLLAPSED is active: FILTER='ZPLC>ZACC', ZF_CONS, ZF_EXCL, ZF_INCL, ZF_FEXCL, ZPLC_MIN/MAX, ZACC_MIN/MAX, ZPLC_OOS; a HISTORY line summarizes counts.
- Sheets table: pinocchio.<RunFlag>.sheets.out (CSV-like ASCII, reproducibility of segment geometry).
- Optional displacement histogram files: pinocchio.<z>.<RunFlag>.disp_hist.out (ASCII; root-only; contains VARPAD context and grid provenance).

## Optimization strategy and rationale
- Replication coarse prefilter: eliminate whole periodic images that cannot intersect the segment shell.
- Lagrangian block culling with variable AABB pad:
  - Early reject blocks using tight radial bounds [dmin,dmax] vs [chi_prev,chi_curr].
  - Exact angular culling (axis piercing + corner enumeration) to skip blocks entirely outside the aperture without false negatives near large apertures.
  - Variable pad scales with sigma8 and redshift; units converted to phys Mpc to match internal position units. On the last segment, collect stats to validate pad adequacy (warn if many particles exceed pad).
- Per-block position cache: reuse prev/curr positions across multiple replications, avoiding recomputation.
- Precompute replication shifts once per segment for all candidates.
- OpenMP strategy: atomics are acceptable for sparse map updates; when contention rises, MASS_MAPS_THREAD_ACCUM trades a bit of memory for fewer atomics by merging once per block.
- Cap representation as RING prefix avoids per-pixel inclusion tests; pixel index bounds-checks are O(1).

## Contracts and error modes (LLM hints)
Inputs:
- Segment index in [1..NMassSheets]; products array must contain prev/curr LPT displacements; PLC geometry initialized; params set; MPI initialized.
Outputs:
- One FITS per processed segment on rank 0; optional ASCII sheets table and histograms.
Failure modes:
- Missing prerequisites (PLC, RECOMPUTE_DISPLACEMENTS, HAVE_CFITSIO) → compile-time error.
- Invalid NSIDE or aperture producing Ncap=0 → map path disabled with warning.
- CFITSIO errors → reported to stderr; function returns non-zero when applicable.
- Crossing interpolation degeneracy (tiny denominator) → no crossing reported for that particle.

## Quick symbol index (where to look)
- Orchestrator: mass_maps_process_segment
- HEALPix maps: mass_maps_init_healpix_maps, mass_maps_write_segment_map, mass_maps_zero_maps, mass_maps_free_maps
- Segments: mass_maps_init_sheets, mass_maps_write_sheet_table
- Replication selection: mass_maps_replication_chi_bounds, mass_maps_select_segment_replications
- Culling helpers: aabb_distance_bounds_to_point
- Products/positions: mass_maps_set_point_from_products_global, mass_maps_compute_prev_curr_positions
- Crossing/pixelize/accumulate: mass_maps_crossing_from_shifted_positions, mass_maps_compute_pixel_from_pos, mass_maps_accumulate_entry_pos
- Filters/diagnostics: mass_maps_get_zacc_global, mass_maps_get_group_id_global, mass_maps_write_filter_keywords, DISP_HISTOGRAM helpers

## Notes for future improvements
- Optional hybrid: switch to per-replication parallelism when many reps pass and few blocks do (or vice-versa).
- Experiment with per-thread compacted lists of changed pixels for faster merges.
- Consider storing reduced precision map deltas per thread to increase cache locality before merge.
